  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will be a qualitative survey to understand the expectations of defibrillator
      patients with regards to their device. It is unknown what ICD (implantable-cardioverter
      defibrillator) patients understand about their device and its purpose, thus we will be
      talking to them about their device. Also, we will be interested in studying their beliefs on
      how the ICD impacts their life expectancy and quality of life.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
